===Noun===
[[Image:Smiley_head_happy.png|80px|thumb|A '''smiley'''.]]
{{en-noun|pl2=smilies}}

# {{rare}} A simplified representation of a smiling face.
# {{Internet}} A sequence of keyboard characters used to represent a person's mood or emotion, especially <tt>[[&nbsp;:)|:)]]</tt> or <tt>[[&nbsp;:-)|:-)]]</tt> or other smiling depiction.
# {{slang}} Having one's throat slit from side to side.
# {{rare}} An improvised street weapon consisting of a length of chain with padlocks and other heavy objects affixed to one end.

'''Note:''' The variant spelling "[[smilie]]" is rare, but the plural form "[[smilies]]" (which is properly the plural of "smilie" or "smily", not "smiley") is common.

